            <h4>Sign Language Translator - Third Year Project</h4>
            <br>
    
            <p>As our third year project, my project partner and I designed and trained Neural Networks to translate Irish Sign Language from prerecorded video into audio.</p>
            <p>The program we produced utilised Convoluted Neural Networks (CNN) and computer vision libraries, such as Keras and Numpy, and was written in Python.</p>
    
            <br>
    
            <p>The functions of this program are as follows:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><p>Converts a video into frames, applying image processing to convert the frames into multi-dimensional arrays and feed them to a trained CNN model.</p></li>
                    <li><p>Accumulates the output of the CNN models to plain text.</p></li>
                    <li><p>Convert the text produced by the CNN into audio, and save the audio file into the current working directory.</p></li>
                </ul>
    
            <br>
    
            <p>The graph and confusion matrix below depict the accuracy of the ensemble model. The orange line in the graph shows the number of correct predictions for that letter sign pair in a test dataset, while the blue line is the number of incorrect predictions for that pair.</p>
            
            <img src="static/nn_result.JPG" alt="" class="graph-image">
    
            <p>This communication channel has the potential to greatly decrease the impacts of deafness, and other communication disorders, which could reduce loneliness and isolation in these communities.</p>
    
            <p>We received a first class honours in this project.</p>
    
